Prime Minister Ariel Sharon announced that he wants to see a million more Jewish immigrants to Israel, bolstering a population of nearly 6.5 million. In a speech on Thursday to an annual gathering of newspaper editors and other journalists, Mr. Sharon said he wanted to focus his efforts on the economy, education and immigration. ''In the next year I want to see a million Jews come from Argentina, France and especially from South Africa,'' he said. Joel Greenberg (NYT)